NEW YORK
By virtue of and pursuant to the authority vested in me as President of the United States, and in order to effectuate further the purposes of the Migratory Bird Conservation Act (45 Stat. 1222), it is ordered that the lands acquired or to be acquired in the following-described area, comprising approximately 7,500 acres in Seneca County, New York, be, and they are hereby, reserved and set apart, subject to valid existing rights, for the use of the Department of Agriculture as a refuge and breeding ground for migratory birds and other wildlife:
Provided
, That any private lands within the area described shall become part of the refuge hereby established upon acquisition of title thereto or control thereof by the United States:
